
## ============================================
## DukerRegistry Worker — API Test Suite
## ============================================
## Toggle between local and production:
@host = http://localhost:8788
# @host = https://api.dukernews.com

## ============================================
## Health Check
## ============================================

### Health
GET {{host}}/

###

### Dev: Inject chain config (for local testing with Anvil)
# Run deploy-local.ts first, then paste addresses here
POST {{host}}/_dev/config
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "chainEid": 31337,
    "dukerRegistryAddress": "0xREPLACE_WITH_PROXY_ADDRESS",
    "dukigenRegistryAddress": "0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000",
    "rpcUrl": "http://127.0.0.1:8545"
}

###

## ============================================
## DukerRegistryService (ConnectRPC)
## ============================================

### GetUsername — by wallet address
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.DukerRegistryService/GetUsername
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "address": "0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266",
    "chainEid": 31337
}

###

### GetUsername — any chain (chainEid = 0)
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.DukerRegistryService/GetUsername
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "address": "0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266",
    "chainEid": 0
}

###

### GetIdentitiesByToken — lookup by tokenId
# tokenId format: (chainEid << 224) | seq
# For local (31337 << 224 | 1) = very large number
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.DukerRegistryService/GetIdentitiesByToken
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "tokenId": "4294998633"
}

###

### NotifyTx — index a DukerRegistry transaction
# Replace tx_hash with actual tx hash from anvil
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.BlockchainSyncService/NotifyTx
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "contract": "DUKER_REGISTRY",
    "txHash": "0xREPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TX_HASH",
    "chainEid": 31337
}

###

## ============================================
## DukigenRegistryService (ConnectRPC)
## ============================================

### GetAgent — by agentId
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.DukigenRegistryService/GetAgent
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "agentId": "1"
}

###

### GetAgents — paginated list
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.DukigenRegistryService/GetAgents
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "page": 1,
    "perPage": 20
}

###

### NotifyTx — index a DukigenRegistry transaction
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.BlockchainSyncService/NotifyTx
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "contract": "DUKIGEN_REGISTRY",
    "txHash": "0xREPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TX_HASH",
    "chainEid": 31337
}

###

### SyncEvents — catch up DukerRegistry
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.BlockchainSyncService/SyncEvents
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "contract": "DUKER_REGISTRY",
    "chainEid": 31337
}

###

### SyncEvents — catch up AlmWorldMinter (DealDukiMinted events)
POST {{host}}/dukiregistry.BlockchainSyncService/SyncEvents
Content-Type: application/json
Connect-Protocol-Version: 1

{
    "contract": "ALM_WORLD_MINTER",
    "chainEid": 31337
}

###

## ============================================
## Devtools (internal ops endpoint)
## ============================================
## Token (production only):
##   node -e "console.log(btoa('YOUR_SECRET:' + Math.floor(Date.now()/1000)))"
## Then set:  @devtools_token = <output>
@devtools_token = REPLACE_WITH_GENERATED_TOKEN

### run_agent_metrics — Dev (no auth required)
POST {{host}}/devtools
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "case": "run_agent_metrics"
}

###

### debug_state — inspect chain configs + DB counters (diagnose zero results)
POST {{host}}/devtools
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "case": "debug_state"
}

###

### run_agent_metrics — Production (requires x-devtools-token)
# POST https://api.dukernews.com/devtools
# Content-Type: application/json
# x-devtools-token: {{devtools_token}}
#
# {
#     "case": "run_agent_metrics"
# }

###
